      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and your<strong> meat-free mince </strong>(remove the paper, if required!) to the pan, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Add your<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>soy sauce</strong> and cook for a further<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>5-6 min or until the meat-free mince is beginning to brown all over – this is your <strong>smoky meat-free mince</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
